{
  "text": "When comparing independent groups, modern improvements on the WilcoxonMann-Whitney (WMW) test are another possibility, which are aimed at making inferences about the probability that a random observation from the first group is less than a random observation from the second. (More details are provided in Section 3.) Additional possibilities are described in [CITATION_1] , some of which are illustrated in Section 4 below.",
